Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 04 of Hand MRI
When I select 'Finding' radio button
Then Finding dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Norm variants / Anomalies' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Add new finding' button is enabled
And 'Accessory carpal bones' radio button is enabled
And 'Carpal coalition' radio button is enabled
And 'Division of carpal bones' radio button is enabled
And 'Norm variants of the os lunatum' radio button is enabled


//Accessory carpal bones

When I select 'Accessory carpal bones' radio button
Then 'Paratrapezium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Trapezium secundarium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Styloidum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Capitatum secundarium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Radiale externum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Centrale' checkbox is enabled
And 'Triangulare' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypotriquetrum' checkbox is enabled

And 'Epitrapezium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Trapezoides secundarium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ossiculum gruberi' checkbox is enabled
And 'Os hamuli proprium' checkbox is enabled
And 'Vesalianum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Ulnare externum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Parascaphoid' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypolunatum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Epilunatum' checkbox is enabled
And 'Epipyramis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Lunula' checkbox is enabled


// Carpal coalition

When I select 'Carpal coalition' radio button
Then 'Involved bones' localizer is enabled
And 'Primary/idiopathic coalitions' radio button is enabled
And 'Secondary coalitions' radio button is enabled

When I click on the localizer
Then a canvas opens
When I select all the 8 bones on the localizer
Then all the 8 bones are selected

When I select 'Primary/idiopathic coalitions' radio button
Then 'Type I: fibro-cartilage fusion' radio button is enabled
And 'Type II: incomplete osseous fusion' radio button is enabled
And 'Type III: complete osseous fusion' radio button is enabled
And 'Type VI: osseous complete fusion (further carpal anomalies)' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Secondary coalitions' radio button
Then 'Postinflammatory' radio button is enabled
And 'Posttraumatic' radio button is enabled



//Division of carpal bones

When I select 'Division of carpal bones' radio button
Then 'Involved bones' localizer is enabled
And 'Bipartitum' radio button is enabled
And 'Tripartitum' radio button is enabled



//Norm variants of the os lunatum

When I select 'Norm variants of the os lunatum' radio button
Then 'Type 1' radio button is enabled
And 'Type 2' radio button is enabled

When I select 'Type 2' radio button
Then 'Chondropathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Bone marrow edema in the os hamatum' checkbox is enabled
